#: templates/store/supply_forecast.html
msgid "stock"
msgstr "stock"

#: templates/store/supply_forecast.html
msgid ""
"Demand = corp ship losses (killboard) over the window, projected to a "
"weekly/monthly rate. Supply cost = cheaper of <span class=\"text-"
"cyan\">build</span> (hull at EVE Ref's full job cost — ME-adjusted materials"
" + install fee — or our local estimate when the API can't price it, marked "
"<span class=\"text-cyan\">~est</span>; modules bought at Jita) or <span "
"class=\"text-muted\">import</span> (full fit at Jita), plus jump-freight to "
"staging priced off the corp rate card. Fair sell = the store's doctrine "
"price (Jita sell × markup). Prices are as fresh as the last market sync; "
"capital freight is approximate."
msgstr ""
"Demande = pertes de vaisseaux de corp (killboard) sur la fenêtre, projetées "
"en taux hebdomadaire/mensuel. Coût d'approvisionnement = le moins cher entre"
" <span class=\"text-cyan\">construire</span> (hull au coût de job complet "
"d'EVE Ref — matériaux ajustés ME + frais d'installation — ou notre "
"estimation locale quand l'API ne peut pas le chiffrer, marqué <span "
"class=\"text-cyan\">~est</span> ; modules achetés à Jita) ou <span "
"class=\"text-muted\">importer</span> (fit complet à Jita), plus le jump-"
"freight vers le staging chiffré selon la grille tarifaire de la corp. Vente "
"équitable = le prix de doctrine de la boutique (vente Jita × marge). Les "
"prix sont aussi récents que la dernière synchro du marché ; le fret de "
"capital est approximatif."

#: templates/store/supply_forecast.html
#, python-format
msgid ""
"No doctrine-ship losses in the last %(window)s days, or no priced doctrine "
